Figure 10 shows the region and a cylindrical shell formed by rotation about the line $x=2$. It has radius $2-x$, circumference $2 \pi(2-x)$, and height $x-x^2$.

FIGURE 10
The volume of the given solid is
$$
\begin{aligned}
V & =\int_0^1 2 \pi(2-x)\left(x-x^2\right) d x \\
& =2 \pi \int_0^1\left(x^3-3 x^2+2 x\right) d x \\
& =2 \pi\left[\frac{x^4}{4}-x^3+x^2\right]_0^1=\frac{\pi}{2}
\end{aligned}
$$
